1
00:00:00,293 --> 00:00:01,993
(There is a problem with the server.)

2
00:00:03,127 --> 00:00:04,227
(Episode 3)

3
00:00:07,972 --> 00:00:08,972
What's going on?

4
00:00:11,972 --> 00:00:13,805
This can't be happening.

5
00:00:16,772 --> 00:00:17,905
What is wrong with this?

6
00:00:23,318 --> 00:00:25,418
Hello. What brings you here?

7
00:00:26,722 --> 00:00:28,155
You don't have much stuff.

8
00:00:28,655 --> 00:00:31,088
Make sure you move out
by next weekend as promised.

9
00:00:31,655 --> 00:00:32,722
Move out? What do you mean?

10
00:00:32,842 --> 00:00:34,508
You need to vacate the room.

11
00:00:34,988 --> 00:00:36,955
You need to leave
so the next tenant can move in.

12
00:00:37,395 --> 00:00:38,929
What? What do you mean by that?

13
00:00:39,459 --> 00:00:41,526
We still have plenty of time left
on the lease.

14
00:00:41,528 --> 00:00:42,861
You didn't know?

15
00:00:44,088 --> 00:00:46,655
That CEO or co-CEO
said he needed the money urgently,

16
00:00:46,655 --> 00:00:48,388
so I already returned the deposit
in advance.

17
00:00:48,499 --> 00:00:50,322
What? No way.

18
00:00:50,555 --> 00:00:52,055
I think there's been
some misunderstanding.

19
00:00:52,055 --> 00:00:53,322
My goodness.

20
00:00:53,322 --> 00:00:56,755
This is why you shouldn't get involved
in other people's business.

21
00:00:56,755 --> 00:00:59,188
Want to see the deposit transfer record?

22
00:00:59,788 --> 00:01:02,255
That can't be right.

23
00:01:02,382 --> 00:01:05,182
No need to drag this out.
Move out by next weekend.

24
00:01:06,788 --> 00:01:09,788
What are we going to do about this mold?

25
00:01:10,855 --> 00:01:14,055
You should've aired the place out
more often.

26
00:01:22,222 --> 00:01:24,822
Ko Dae Chi as chairman?
What are you talking about?

27
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:26,475
Min Ho's mom said so.

28
00:01:26,915 --> 00:01:28,515
She said her husband
would be the next chairman.

29
00:01:29,655 --> 00:01:31,155
The Chairman is still alive and well.

30
00:01:32,002 --> 00:01:33,302
Don't ever say something like that again.

31
00:01:33,822 --> 00:01:37,188
That may be true, but at his age,
with terminal lung cancer...

32
00:01:37,261 --> 00:01:39,095
I'm warning you.

33
00:01:39,988 --> 00:01:42,655
From now on, don't go
to the Chairman's house, okay?

34
00:01:42,655 --> 00:01:43,688
Seriously!

35
00:01:44,201 --> 00:01:47,301
How could I not? We aren't animals.

36
00:01:47,686 --> 00:01:48,886
If you don't know what gratitude is...

37
00:01:49,035 --> 00:01:50,402
Please, enough with that "gratitude" talk!

38
00:01:52,822 --> 00:01:54,742
What's going on? Did something happen?

39
00:01:56,088 --> 00:01:57,255
No, it's nothing.

40
00:01:58,622 --> 00:01:59,622
You're late.

41
00:02:00,288 --> 00:02:02,688
I've been busy lately
with the mergers and acquisitions deal.

42
00:02:02,688 --> 00:02:03,722
Mergers and acquisitions?

43
00:02:03,722 --> 00:02:06,655
It's nothing major. A report will go
to the Chairman's office soon.

44
00:02:07,055 --> 00:02:09,122
All right. Don't overdo it.

45
00:02:11,222 --> 00:02:13,788
Honey, don't forget what I said.

46
00:02:13,861 --> 00:02:16,128
If the Chairman passes away,

47
00:02:16,455 --> 00:02:18,822
is it wrong to say Min Ho's dad
will take that seat?

48
00:02:19,388 --> 00:02:21,422
And it was Min Ho's mom who said that!

49
00:02:21,422 --> 00:02:24,255
What are you talking about?
The Chairman is dying?

50
00:02:24,382 --> 00:02:26,982
Apparently, he has stage four lung cancer.

51
00:02:27,588 --> 00:02:30,588
On top of that, he's given up treatment
and was discharged.

52
00:02:31,215 --> 00:02:33,348
What? Is that true, Dad?

53
00:02:34,002 --> 00:02:36,115
Keep this strictly confidential for now.

54
00:02:36,982 --> 00:02:38,549
Wait until the Chairman announces it.

55
00:02:39,681 --> 00:02:40,715
How did this happen?

56
00:02:45,355 --> 00:02:47,788
Yes, Gyeol. You are coming back?

57
00:02:49,328 --> 00:02:50,495
That's a good decision.

58
00:02:52,782 --> 00:02:54,015
Then what about your work there?

59
00:02:54,455 --> 00:02:56,222
This isn't the time to be thinking
about my own work.

60
00:02:56,674 --> 00:02:58,574
I'll contact you again
as soon as I book my flight.

61
00:02:59,489 --> 00:03:00,489
All right.

62
00:03:00,934 --> 00:03:02,301
The Chairman will be very happy.

63
00:03:03,155 --> 00:03:04,155
Bye.

64
00:03:04,588 --> 00:03:06,422
Looks like Gyeol heard the news too.

65
00:03:07,055 --> 00:03:09,322
He hasn't come back once
in the past ten years,

66
00:03:09,395 --> 00:03:10,928
and now suddenly he's coming back.

67
00:03:11,188 --> 00:03:12,455
The Chairman called for him.

68
00:03:13,121 --> 00:03:14,121
My goodness.

69
00:03:15,135 --> 00:03:18,501
He must've wanted to see Gyeol
before the end.

70
00:03:19,182 --> 00:03:20,448
When is he coming?

71
00:03:21,155 --> 00:03:23,788
Soon, as soon as he wraps things up there.

72
00:03:25,755 --> 00:03:27,355
Seung Ri, get some rest now.

73
00:03:27,755 --> 00:03:29,222
- Yes, good night, Dad.
- You too.

74
00:03:31,322 --> 00:03:34,955
Right, Min Ho is going on a blind date
with the second daughter of Samho Group.

75
00:03:35,428 --> 00:03:36,528
So?

76
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:38,209
Can't you just say yes to him?

77
00:03:39,022 --> 00:03:41,488
He's been devoted to you
since he was little.

78
00:03:42,161 --> 00:03:45,895
Frankly, Min Ho is the future chairman
of Kangsu Group.

79
00:03:46,155 --> 00:03:47,788
I'm going to my room. Good night.

80
00:03:49,522 --> 00:03:51,322
Hey, Seo Seung Ri!

81
00:03:52,755 --> 00:03:54,027
Where have you been until now?

82
00:03:54,029 --> 00:03:55,562
Don't talk to me. I'm busy!

83
00:03:56,755 --> 00:03:59,222
Yeah, I'm sure you are.

84
00:04:00,302 --> 00:04:02,568
They say even unemployed people
can die of overwork.

85
00:04:04,388 --> 00:04:05,955
None of you are good for anything.

86
00:04:08,255 --> 00:04:09,488
Don't tell me...

87
00:04:14,922 --> 00:04:16,888
Ideas never come to me in my room,

88
00:04:17,274 --> 00:04:18,908
but the moment I go to a cafe,
they just pour out.

89
00:04:23,122 --> 00:04:24,588
Haven't I hit you enough?

90
00:04:24,588 --> 00:04:26,809
You still want more?

91
00:04:26,895 --> 00:04:29,422
I told you not to wear
your sister's clothes!

92
00:04:29,422 --> 00:04:30,422
Mom!

93
00:04:30,755 --> 00:04:33,055
You're destroying an artist's inspiration.

94
00:04:33,122 --> 00:04:34,389
This is barbaric!

95
00:04:36,056 --> 00:04:38,089
An artist's inspiration, my foot.

96
00:04:38,854 --> 00:04:41,188
If I catch you one more time...

97
00:04:41,588 --> 00:04:42,988
Stop wearing your sister's clothes!

98
00:04:43,288 --> 00:04:44,955
Get out, will you?

99
00:04:45,155 --> 00:04:46,255
- Get out.
- You never listen!

100
00:04:46,294 --> 00:04:47,294
Just get out.

101
00:05:13,098 --> 00:05:14,264
Sergeant Ko's girlfriend?

102
00:05:14,266 --> 00:05:15,066
(Unit 864)

103
00:05:15,068 --> 00:05:16,968
Nice to meet you, ma'am. Salute!

104
00:05:17,255 --> 00:05:19,022
She's not my girlfriend.
She's like a little sister to me.

105
00:05:19,588 --> 00:05:23,222
Come on, what kind of sister
writes letters almost every day?

106
00:05:24,202 --> 00:05:26,435
Since you came all this way,
you should take a photo.

107
00:05:26,755 --> 00:05:27,755
Give me your phone.

108
00:05:27,755 --> 00:05:29,155
Hey, we don't need a photo.

109
00:05:29,155 --> 00:05:30,455
All right, stand close together.

110
00:05:30,629 --> 00:05:32,955
Here I go. Get closer.

111
00:05:32,955 --> 00:05:35,155
Here we go. One, two, three.

112
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,588
That's enough. You should head back now.

113
00:05:38,681 --> 00:05:39,681
It's almost curfew.

114
00:05:41,455 --> 00:05:44,188
Enjoy your time. Salute!

115
00:05:45,588 --> 00:05:48,022
Seriously, I told you
she's not my girlfriend.

116
00:05:49,088 --> 00:05:51,155
Sorry, he's a bit cheeky.

117
00:05:52,288 --> 00:05:53,488
Why am I your sister?

118
00:05:55,755 --> 00:05:58,322
I like you, Gyeol.

119
00:05:59,296 --> 00:06:01,429
I don't want to be your sister anymore.

120
00:06:02,188 --> 00:06:04,088
Seung Ri, I'm sorry.

121
00:06:04,622 --> 00:06:07,055
But don't come here anymore.
And don't write letters either.

122
00:06:07,522 --> 00:06:08,688
Even if you come to visit,
I won't come out.

123
00:06:09,488 --> 00:06:11,422
Why? Why do I have to do that?

124
00:06:11,495 --> 00:06:12,495
I told you.

125
00:06:12,935 --> 00:06:15,722
I see you as a sister, but if you don't...

126
00:06:15,722 --> 00:06:17,688
Is it because of Min Ho?

127
00:06:18,155 --> 00:06:19,388
What are you talking about?

128
00:06:20,415 --> 00:06:21,835
I should go back now.

129
00:06:21,837 --> 00:06:23,404
Hurry, before you miss the last train.

130
00:06:26,542 --> 00:06:29,042
No matter how much you push me away,
I won't budge.

131
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:31,188
Even if you don't reply,
I'll keep writing.

132
00:06:31,188 --> 00:06:32,888
Even if you refuse visits,
I'll keep coming.

133
00:06:33,555 --> 00:06:34,555
Listen carefully, Seo Seung Ri.

134
00:06:35,055 --> 00:06:37,422
You've never been a woman to me.

135
00:06:38,322 --> 00:06:40,755
If you keep this up,
we won't be able to see each other.

136
00:06:41,655 --> 00:06:43,055
I'll get going. Take care.

137
00:06:44,928 --> 00:06:45,928
Gyeol!

138
00:07:06,088 --> 00:07:08,422
The watch Gyeol gave me stopped.

139
00:07:09,569 --> 00:07:10,702
I should get it repaired.

140
00:07:15,422 --> 00:07:19,188
The clock will start again, and so can we.

141
00:07:25,422 --> 00:07:27,055
Do you really have to go right now?

142
00:07:27,128 --> 00:07:28,428
Then what about our project?

143
00:07:29,455 --> 00:07:33,175
I'm sorry, but if I don't go now,
I'll regret it for the rest of my life.

144
00:07:33,582 --> 00:07:35,855
Just finish this project first
and then go.

145
00:07:35,935 --> 00:07:37,635
You're just getting started now.

146
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:38,875
By then, it'll be too late.

147
00:07:39,141 --> 00:07:41,275
My beginning is someone else's ending.

148
00:07:46,988 --> 00:07:48,255
You're not asleep yet?

149
00:07:48,822 --> 00:07:50,288
No. Have you eaten?

150
00:07:50,922 --> 00:07:53,122
Come on, look at the time. I'll go up.

151
00:07:53,855 --> 00:07:55,955
Hey, sit down for a moment.

152
00:07:57,388 --> 00:07:58,855
I'm a bit tired.

153
00:08:02,422 --> 00:08:03,422
You.

154
00:08:04,695 --> 00:08:06,395
What do you like so much about him?

155
00:08:06,921 --> 00:08:09,655
- What?
- You had a crush on him for five years.

156
00:08:10,329 --> 00:08:13,696
What exactly do you like about him?
How much and why?

157
00:08:13,962 --> 00:08:15,928
What is this, an essay test?

158
00:08:16,747 --> 00:08:18,914
Well, we've had the same goal...

159
00:08:19,255 --> 00:08:20,988
and worked together for a long time.

160
00:08:21,388 --> 00:08:24,342
Even if you've known someone
for a long time,

161
00:08:24,695 --> 00:08:28,995
dating them and working with them
are two different things.

162
00:08:30,095 --> 00:08:33,022
Someone as naive
and inexperienced as you...

163
00:08:33,022 --> 00:08:36,522
Mom, why don't you trust me?

164
00:08:37,641 --> 00:08:38,641
What?

165
00:08:39,522 --> 00:08:42,053
Is this because of what I
said this morning?

166
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:44,822
No, it's not that.
You're always like this.

167
00:08:45,288 --> 00:08:47,855
Everything I do is always clumsy,
insignificant, and unreliable to you.

168
00:08:48,455 --> 00:08:49,822
Hey, Cho Eun Ae.

169
00:08:52,122 --> 00:08:54,322
I'm sorry. I went too far.

170
00:08:55,222 --> 00:08:57,655
I know you're just worried about me.

171
00:08:58,748 --> 00:08:59,848
As long as you know that.

172
00:09:01,055 --> 00:09:02,788
Did you tell him about inviting him
this weekend?

173
00:09:02,981 --> 00:09:05,915
Right, I don't think
this weekend will work.

174
00:09:06,121 --> 00:09:07,821
He went back to his hometown today.

175
00:09:08,689 --> 00:09:09,689
His hometown?

176
00:09:10,655 --> 00:09:12,535
Then find out when he's available next...

177
00:09:12,537 --> 00:09:13,837
and set another date.

178
00:09:14,955 --> 00:09:15,955
Okay.

179
00:09:17,188 --> 00:09:18,188
What is that?

180
00:09:19,468 --> 00:09:20,468
What?

181
00:09:21,015 --> 00:09:23,448
It's a scarf. It's for you.

182
00:09:25,088 --> 00:09:26,088
A scarf?

183
00:09:27,015 --> 00:09:29,249
Did he get you this to win me over?

184
00:09:29,322 --> 00:09:32,288
No, I bought it. I'm going upstairs.

185
00:09:33,242 --> 00:09:35,776
Hey, where did you get the money?

186
00:09:38,755 --> 00:09:41,122
Is Eun Ae home?

187
00:09:41,722 --> 00:09:43,888
Yes. She even...

188
00:09:44,621 --> 00:09:45,954
bought me a gift out of the blue.

189
00:09:50,561 --> 00:09:51,561
My goodness.

190
00:09:52,015 --> 00:09:55,815
Honey, isn't this a luxury brand?
It is, right?

191
00:09:56,522 --> 00:09:57,522
I'm not sure.

192
00:09:58,128 --> 00:09:59,895
Like I'd be able to tell.

193
00:10:00,789 --> 00:10:02,522
She must be crazy.

194
00:10:03,321 --> 00:10:05,209
This must've been really expensive.

195
00:10:06,555 --> 00:10:08,122
I should tell her to return it right away.

196
00:10:08,762 --> 00:10:10,788
She bought something for her mom.

197
00:10:10,788 --> 00:10:12,722
Why are you talking about returning it?

198
00:10:13,075 --> 00:10:15,088
There's a limit to how reckless
she can be.

199
00:10:15,088 --> 00:10:16,522
She works herself to the bone

200
00:10:16,522 --> 00:10:19,355
and hasn't even been properly paid once.

201
00:10:19,355 --> 00:10:21,822
Please stop. You'll hurt her feelings.

202
00:10:23,055 --> 00:10:25,755
- Eun Ae just won't say anything.
- What?

203
00:10:26,255 --> 00:10:28,455
Even this morning, about her boyfriend.

204
00:10:28,788 --> 00:10:31,422
She got confessed to
by the guy she's liked for years.

205
00:10:31,549 --> 00:10:33,182
You could've just congratulated her.

206
00:10:33,855 --> 00:10:35,755
I'm just worried.

207
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:38,435
About what? What are you so worried about?

208
00:10:38,855 --> 00:10:40,722
She's been too kind since she was young,

209
00:10:40,722 --> 00:10:44,422
always giving in and taking the loss.

210
00:10:44,922 --> 00:10:47,022
With all the academy and tutoring fees
for Eun Hyeong and Eun Nim,

211
00:10:47,022 --> 00:10:48,973
she knew we were struggling,

212
00:10:48,975 --> 00:10:51,955
so she refused to go to academies,
no matter what.

213
00:10:51,955 --> 00:10:53,722
So, you see?

214
00:10:54,122 --> 00:10:55,822
She's so thoughtful...

215
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:57,275
I don't like it.

216
00:10:58,055 --> 00:10:59,407
It already hurts seeing her like that
at home,

217
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:02,188
so I'm worried
she'll get taken advantage of

218
00:11:02,188 --> 00:11:03,688
outside too.

219
00:11:04,022 --> 00:11:06,088
Eun Ae isn't that careless.

220
00:11:06,622 --> 00:11:08,455
She's strong-minded and smart.

221
00:11:08,922 --> 00:11:12,788
Kids grow as much as
their parents trust them.

222
00:11:13,309 --> 00:11:15,342
- So please...
- Gosh.

223
00:11:16,155 --> 00:11:18,222
You're really on a roll today.

224
00:11:18,455 --> 00:11:21,122
Yes, sir.
I'll take your wise words to heart.

225
00:11:23,609 --> 00:11:24,775
Anyway...

226
00:11:25,822 --> 00:11:28,575
How much can you borrow from the company?

227
00:11:29,622 --> 00:11:32,622
What? Borrow money?

228
00:11:32,822 --> 00:11:34,122
Dating is one thing,

229
00:11:34,122 --> 00:11:37,488
but at their age,
they'll be thinking about marriage.

230
00:11:40,055 --> 00:11:42,055
I've been running the numbers all day,

231
00:11:43,022 --> 00:11:45,722
but all our money is tied up.

232
00:11:46,375 --> 00:11:49,241
And if marriage actually comes up...

233
00:11:50,588 --> 00:11:53,555
That's something to worry about later.

234
00:11:53,869 --> 00:11:55,369
Geez, I'm tired.

235
00:11:56,449 --> 00:11:57,449
Geez.

236
00:11:57,842 --> 00:11:58,855
Gosh.

237
00:12:00,074 --> 00:12:01,074
Honey.

238
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:05,855
Should I just close
the real estate office?

239
00:12:08,888 --> 00:12:09,955
Maybe it's the economy,

240
00:12:10,421 --> 00:12:14,055
but these days I only get
one or two deals a month at most.

241
00:12:14,388 --> 00:12:15,922
And even those fall through half the time.

242
00:12:16,722 --> 00:12:20,122
Wouldn't it be better
to just rent out the place instead?

243
00:12:24,222 --> 00:12:25,222
You're already asleep?

244
00:12:30,455 --> 00:12:32,288
Ji Hun,
why aren't you answering your phone?

245
00:12:33,222 --> 00:12:34,688
Please call me as soon as you see this.

246
00:12:35,728 --> 00:12:37,295
Why isn't the server opening?

247
00:12:37,988 --> 00:12:39,988
The landlady came by.

248
00:12:40,054 --> 00:12:42,188
She said I have to move out.
What's going on?

249
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:44,888
No way...

250
00:12:46,955 --> 00:12:49,522
Joy, I can't reach him.

251
00:12:50,355 --> 00:12:53,089
The server's down,
and he's already cleared out the office.

252
00:12:53,755 --> 00:12:55,322
Nothing could've happened, right?

253
00:12:55,788 --> 00:12:57,155
There's no way, right?

254
00:12:57,242 --> 00:13:00,142
There's a saying that goes,
"What you fear comes true."

255
00:13:00,522 --> 00:13:01,755
A similar saying is...

256
00:13:01,755 --> 00:13:03,422
Hey, are you really doing this too?

257
00:13:03,422 --> 00:13:05,722
There's no way! No!

258
00:13:09,455 --> 00:13:10,942
- What are you doing right now?
- Huh?

259
00:13:11,235 --> 00:13:13,035
Don't you know our walls are thin?

260
00:13:13,455 --> 00:13:16,672
Sorry. Was I disturbing your studying?

261
00:13:17,368 --> 00:13:19,035
Is something not working out?

262
00:13:19,522 --> 00:13:20,855
No, everything's fine.

263
00:13:21,575 --> 00:13:23,342
Don't tell me he called off
the relationship.

264
00:13:23,655 --> 00:13:26,155
Seriously! Get out. I said get out!

265
00:13:26,155 --> 00:13:28,522
Look at you. This is really suspicious.

266
00:13:28,662 --> 00:13:30,062
I'm guessing...

267
00:13:30,255 --> 00:13:32,988
Speaking of thin walls,

268
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:36,595
what are you even typing every night?

269
00:13:36,988 --> 00:13:38,922
Do you know how many times I wake up
because of that?

270
00:13:39,255 --> 00:13:41,322
You can hear that?

271
00:13:41,635 --> 00:13:44,861
What kind of med student
types all night long?

272
00:13:45,588 --> 00:13:48,088
Are you preparing
for a typing test instead?

273
00:13:48,088 --> 00:13:51,355
It just helps me memorize better...

274
00:13:51,421 --> 00:13:53,654
if I type instead of just memorizing.

275
00:13:55,801 --> 00:13:58,501
Anyway, whatever it is, hang in there.
You can do it!

276
00:13:58,882 --> 00:13:59,882
Come on.

277
00:14:02,682 --> 00:14:04,615
Like that is going to help.

278
00:14:06,235 --> 00:14:07,255
I should just sleep.

279
00:14:11,695 --> 00:14:13,128
I'll get through to him tomorrow.

280
00:14:13,729 --> 00:14:15,329
There must be some reason.

281
00:14:21,255 --> 00:14:23,155
(Kangsu Construction)

282
00:14:23,155 --> 00:14:24,222
Grandpa.

283
00:14:24,742 --> 00:14:26,742
What kind of patient goes to work?

284
00:14:27,421 --> 00:14:29,388
This isn't the time for you
to be worrying about work.

285
00:14:30,268 --> 00:14:33,502
We're at the office. Watch how you speak.

286
00:14:34,888 --> 00:14:36,088
I'm sorry, Chairman.

287
00:14:38,261 --> 00:14:42,327
But for cancer patients,
rest is the most important thing.

288
00:14:42,329 --> 00:14:43,762
You mustn't overexert yourself.

289
00:14:44,188 --> 00:14:46,322
For the time being, forget about work...

290
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:47,768
and just rest at home.

291
00:14:48,355 --> 00:14:51,555
There's a mountain of work to do,
and you want me to lie around already?

292
00:14:52,635 --> 00:14:55,447
If this
is about the retirement community project,

293
00:14:55,449 --> 00:14:56,955
Min Ho and I can handle it.

294
00:14:57,968 --> 00:15:00,135
So please, go back to the hospital.

295
00:15:00,855 --> 00:15:03,155
Please, just listen to your children.

296
00:15:03,742 --> 00:15:04,742
Stop.

297
00:15:06,054 --> 00:15:08,154
Let me warn you.

298
00:15:08,955 --> 00:15:11,655
If any rumors about my health get leaked,

299
00:15:12,355 --> 00:15:13,488
you're all finished.

300
00:15:14,155 --> 00:15:16,088
Of course, we understand.

301
00:15:16,088 --> 00:15:18,022
We know how much an owner's health risk...

302
00:15:18,022 --> 00:15:21,155
affects stock prices.

303
00:15:26,022 --> 00:15:28,088
Chairman, Lawyer Kang is here.

304
00:15:28,281 --> 00:15:29,481
Let him in.

305
00:15:30,628 --> 00:15:34,228
Why is Lawyer Kang here all of a sudden?

306
00:15:34,988 --> 00:15:36,755
I called him because I needed him!

307
00:15:38,075 --> 00:15:39,075
You may leave.

308
00:15:48,435 --> 00:15:52,056
Why did he call Lawyer Kang?

309
00:15:53,022 --> 00:15:55,188
I'm not sure.

310
00:15:55,188 --> 00:15:57,055
Come on, don't be like that.

311
00:15:57,722 --> 00:15:59,122
Are you upset
because of what I said yesterday?

312
00:16:00,855 --> 00:16:02,186
I was just shocked,

313
00:16:02,188 --> 00:16:04,688
so I got a bit carried away.
Try to understand.

314
00:16:04,988 --> 00:16:06,054
I really don't know.

315
00:16:06,422 --> 00:16:08,155
You really hold a grudge, don't you?

316
00:16:11,955 --> 00:16:12,955
Hey, Gyeol.

317
00:16:14,481 --> 00:16:15,581
Everything's been taken care of?

318
00:16:16,482 --> 00:16:18,582
All right. I'll see you that day.

319
00:16:19,888 --> 00:16:23,188
What was that? Is Gyeol coming back?

320
00:16:24,395 --> 00:16:26,228
Why all of a sudden? What for?

321
00:16:27,522 --> 00:16:28,588
The Chairman called him.

322
00:16:28,588 --> 00:16:31,622
I think the Chairman
might have something else in mind.

323
00:16:32,402 --> 00:16:34,069
Something else? Like what?

324
00:16:35,048 --> 00:16:36,248
How would I know?

325
00:16:37,589 --> 00:16:40,622
More importantly,
that mergers and acquisitions deal.

326
00:16:41,275 --> 00:16:43,120
It's really good for the company, right?

327
00:16:43,122 --> 00:16:44,222
Of course.

328
00:16:44,788 --> 00:16:48,122
We picked up a program
for the retirement community dirt cheap.

329
00:16:48,761 --> 00:16:49,761
It's a complete success.

330
00:16:50,355 --> 00:16:53,662
Good. Then pass the materials
to PR right away...

331
00:16:54,075 --> 00:16:55,275
and get a press release out immediately.

332
00:16:56,422 --> 00:16:59,088
You need to show Grandpa your capabilities
as soon as possible.

333
00:16:59,422 --> 00:17:00,455
Yes, sir!

334
00:17:01,168 --> 00:17:02,168
That's it.

335
00:17:04,155 --> 00:17:06,455
What a solid guy.

336
00:17:07,355 --> 00:17:08,422
Wait a second.

337
00:17:08,821 --> 00:17:11,621
He called Gyeol back.

338
00:17:12,655 --> 00:17:13,688
Then I should make a call too.

339
00:17:16,322 --> 00:17:19,282
Mr. Ju, come in for a moment.

340
00:17:26,022 --> 00:17:27,388
Yes, you called?

341
00:17:28,688 --> 00:17:30,822
- Come here.
- What?

342
00:17:32,494 --> 00:17:34,428
Get closer just for a second.

343
00:17:34,436 --> 00:17:35,496
Geez.

344
00:17:35,588 --> 00:17:37,688
My goodness.

345
00:17:38,895 --> 00:17:42,695
Lawyer Kang
just went into the Chairman's office.

346
00:17:43,155 --> 00:17:45,088
Could you find out what that's about?

347
00:17:47,662 --> 00:17:48,662
Geez.

348
00:17:48,962 --> 00:17:50,828
Are you seriously asking me...

349
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:53,795
to spy on the Chairman's office?

350
00:17:54,341 --> 00:17:55,341
Come on.

351
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,362
What a way to frame things.

352
00:17:56,364 --> 00:17:57,998
Who said anything about spying?

353
00:17:59,215 --> 00:18:01,581
I just meant sharing some information!

354
00:18:02,528 --> 00:18:03,928
If you're so confident,

355
00:18:04,662 --> 00:18:06,595
why don't you ask him yourself?

356
00:18:07,595 --> 00:18:08,595
So, you can't?

357
00:18:09,595 --> 00:18:11,295
I know you used to be one
of my father's people,

358
00:18:11,295 --> 00:18:13,295
but you're my secretary now.

359
00:18:13,562 --> 00:18:17,228
If you're not going to do what I say,
then just hand in your resignation!

360
00:18:18,115 --> 00:18:19,348
Resignation...

361
00:18:24,695 --> 00:18:27,395
I'll look into it as far as I can,

362
00:18:28,768 --> 00:18:30,535
but don't expect too much.

363
00:18:31,295 --> 00:18:32,295
Okay then!

364
00:18:33,928 --> 00:18:37,195
If it weren't for my father,
I'd fire him on the spot.

365
00:18:37,195 --> 00:18:38,795
He's so slow, it's driving me crazy.

366
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:41,241
Geez, seriously.

367
00:18:45,028 --> 00:18:46,028
Where is everyone?

368
00:18:46,895 --> 00:18:48,395
They went out for lunch.

369
00:18:49,162 --> 00:18:50,562
Why didn't you go, Ms. Seo?

370
00:18:50,562 --> 00:18:52,362
I'll go after I finish this.

371
00:18:52,362 --> 00:18:54,328
Really? Then want to grab lunch with me?

372
00:18:55,048 --> 00:18:57,581
Don't tell me you already
have plans again today.

373
00:18:57,728 --> 00:18:58,828
I'm not hungry.

374
00:19:01,301 --> 00:19:04,468
Why do you hate eating with me so much?

375
00:19:05,202 --> 00:19:07,046
We used to eat together all the time
when we were kids.

376
00:19:07,048 --> 00:19:09,248
Your family would come over to our house.
Don't you remember?

377
00:19:09,928 --> 00:19:11,795
Yes, which is why I don't like it.

378
00:19:12,322 --> 00:19:14,322
They're not very pleasant memories for me.

379
00:19:14,528 --> 00:19:17,695
Seo Seung Ri,
that's just your inferiority complex.

380
00:19:17,962 --> 00:19:18,995
Come on, don't be like that.

381
00:19:21,562 --> 00:19:24,162
All right, fine.

382
00:19:26,028 --> 00:19:27,262
I knew you'd say that.

383
00:19:29,195 --> 00:19:30,195
Ta-da.

384
00:19:32,762 --> 00:19:35,662
Right. Sort the Lucky Joy Tech
acquisition materials...

385
00:19:35,662 --> 00:19:38,162
and send them to PR today.

386
00:19:38,162 --> 00:19:39,162
Yes, sir.

387
00:19:39,795 --> 00:19:41,462
You should eat this first.

388
00:19:41,462 --> 00:19:43,128
Here you go.

389
00:19:43,995 --> 00:19:44,995
Wait a second.

390
00:19:48,028 --> 00:19:49,028
Hello, Mother.

391
00:19:50,642 --> 00:19:51,975
No, I'm not going.

392
00:19:52,842 --> 00:19:53,842
I said I'm not going!

393
00:19:55,828 --> 00:19:57,519
What do you mean you're not going?

394
00:19:57,895 --> 00:20:00,462
I already talked it over with them,
so just go, okay?

395
00:20:02,628 --> 00:20:04,328
Hello? Hey!

396
00:20:05,795 --> 00:20:08,795
Gosh, this is stressing me out.

397
00:20:09,928 --> 00:20:11,728
Maid, I need some ice water.

398
00:20:14,528 --> 00:20:15,528
Gosh, stress.

399
00:20:21,095 --> 00:20:22,628
Where did the maid go?

400
00:20:22,862 --> 00:20:24,895
She's busy making kimchi.

401
00:20:25,775 --> 00:20:29,375
You should at least get your own water.

402
00:20:30,302 --> 00:20:33,135
I didn't ask you to bring it for me,
but you did.

403
00:20:33,669 --> 00:20:37,102
You can't force Min Ho into this.

404
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:39,608
They say parents can't win
against their children.

405
00:20:39,728 --> 00:20:41,528
Are you telling me...

406
00:20:41,728 --> 00:20:44,395
to accept Seung Ri as my daughter-in-law
because Min Ho wants it?

407
00:20:44,695 --> 00:20:48,362
Well, that would only happen
if Seung Ri says yes to Min Ho.

408
00:20:48,362 --> 00:20:50,628
Are you trying to provoke me right now?

409
00:20:50,628 --> 00:20:54,395
I'm going to the clinic,
so take care of lunch yourself.

410
00:21:05,095 --> 00:21:06,462
My blood pressure is rising!

411
00:21:06,795 --> 00:21:08,595
Gosh, my blood pressure.

412
00:21:09,395 --> 00:21:12,028
Calm down, Eun Su Jeong.
You can handle this.

413
00:21:20,928 --> 00:21:23,595
The mountain is a mountain,
the water is water.

414
00:21:26,428 --> 00:21:28,762
The mountain is a mountain,
the water is water.

415
00:21:34,162 --> 00:21:36,562
(Realty Academy Certificate,
Barista Certification)

416
00:21:36,562 --> 00:21:38,395
(Licensed Realtor Certificate,
National Technical License, Certificate)

417
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:43,628
Today is Chapter 1,
understanding care recipients.

418
00:21:44,481 --> 00:21:45,481
Are you busy?

419
00:21:46,195 --> 00:21:47,628
No, I'm almost done.

420
00:21:48,462 --> 00:21:49,995
What are you studying so hard?

421
00:21:51,062 --> 00:21:53,862
I'm taking an online course
to get a caregiver certification.

422
00:21:54,515 --> 00:21:57,628
I hate studying more than anything.

423
00:21:57,975 --> 00:21:59,875
How can you keep studying like that?

424
00:22:00,762 --> 00:22:03,528
What are you talking about?
Studying is fun.

425
00:22:04,001 --> 00:22:05,801
You can learn something new
that you didn't know before.

426
00:22:06,395 --> 00:22:07,395
I see.

427
00:22:08,222 --> 00:22:11,255
That must be why your children
were all good at studying.

428
00:22:11,362 --> 00:22:13,062
Eun Ae was good at studying?

429
00:22:13,062 --> 00:22:15,395
Not compared to Eun Hyeong or Eun Nim,

430
00:22:15,728 --> 00:22:17,762
but she was always
in the top ten in her class.

431
00:22:17,832 --> 00:22:20,228
Really? What about you?

432
00:22:21,028 --> 00:22:23,595
I was always in the top ten,
from the bottom.

433
00:22:25,295 --> 00:22:28,162
Grandma made radish noodles for lunch,
so she asked you to come over.

434
00:22:28,295 --> 00:22:29,562
She even made mine?

435
00:22:29,895 --> 00:22:32,262
All right, I'll come after I finish this.

436
00:22:32,262 --> 00:22:33,262
Okay.

437
00:22:38,628 --> 00:22:39,762
(Kangsu Construction
successfully acquired Lucky Joy Tech.)

438
00:22:39,762 --> 00:22:42,595
What? What is this?

439
00:22:47,528 --> 00:22:49,128
Why isn't she answering?

440
00:22:50,195 --> 00:22:53,362
What are you doing?
The noodles are getting soggy.

441
00:22:53,582 --> 00:22:55,515
Grandma, wait a second.
The noodles aren't important right now.

442
00:22:56,462 --> 00:22:58,928
Why do you always make me food too?

443
00:22:59,062 --> 00:23:02,262
Don't worry, it's nothing.

444
00:23:02,262 --> 00:23:03,495
Just come over quickly.

445
00:23:03,962 --> 00:23:05,535
You two go ahead and eat without me.

446
00:23:06,395 --> 00:23:07,562
Hey, hey!

447
00:23:08,069 --> 00:23:10,349
What's going on with her all of a sudden?

448
00:23:11,495 --> 00:23:14,295
Hello. This is Eun Ae.

449
00:23:14,928 --> 00:23:17,395
Hey, nerd, what's up?
Calling me out of the blue.

450
00:23:17,695 --> 00:23:20,562
Come on. I was the engineering goddess.

451
00:23:22,242 --> 00:23:24,662
Have you seen Ji Hun recently...

452
00:23:24,662 --> 00:23:27,428
or heard from him?

453
00:23:28,095 --> 00:23:30,828
No. Aren't you working with him?

454
00:23:31,395 --> 00:23:34,228
I am, but I suddenly can't reach him.

455
00:23:34,895 --> 00:23:37,195
His hometown is Wanpyeong, right?

456
00:23:37,795 --> 00:23:39,428
Could I get the exact address?

457
00:23:40,362 --> 00:23:41,528
Hold on.

458
00:23:43,928 --> 00:23:45,962
Jini-ri, Suan-myeon.

459
00:23:46,495 --> 00:23:48,128
Yes, thank you.

460
00:23:49,648 --> 00:23:50,648
Hey, you little brat.

461
00:23:50,822 --> 00:23:53,222
Who were you talking to?
I couldn't get through.

462
00:23:53,362 --> 00:23:54,695
Why? What's going on?

463
00:23:55,055 --> 00:23:57,688
Didn't you say Kangsu Construction
was investing in you?

464
00:23:57,895 --> 00:23:58,928
Yeah, why?

465
00:23:59,801 --> 00:24:02,134
Then what's this article about?
What is this?

466
00:24:02,895 --> 00:24:05,195
(Kangsu Construction
successfully acquired Lucky Joy Tech.)

467
00:24:09,295 --> 00:24:12,829
How did this happen? Acquisition?

468
00:24:14,249 --> 00:24:15,549
You didn't know either?

469
00:24:16,128 --> 00:24:17,595
How could that be?

470
00:24:19,628 --> 00:24:21,395
Where is Ji Hun? Where is he?

471
00:24:25,295 --> 00:24:27,328
Hey, Cho Eun Ae. Where are you going?

472
00:24:29,568 --> 00:24:30,761
(Shuttle Bus)

473
00:24:54,034 --> 00:24:56,168
Excuse me, is anyone here?

474
00:25:00,095 --> 00:25:01,128
Who are you?

475
00:25:01,222 --> 00:25:04,022
Excuse me, is this Han Ji Hun's house?

476
00:25:04,315 --> 00:25:05,982
Yes, it is. And you are?

477
00:25:06,022 --> 00:25:09,689
Hello, I'm Cho Eun Ae. I work with him.

478
00:25:09,962 --> 00:25:12,495
I see, the junior he's in business with.

479
00:25:12,921 --> 00:25:14,421
Congratulations.

480
00:25:15,235 --> 00:25:16,835
- Sorry?
- I heard your company...

481
00:25:17,162 --> 00:25:20,528
got acquired by a major corporation.
They even offered you a job.

482
00:25:20,895 --> 00:25:24,662
He came by suddenly the other day
and even handed over a thick envelope.

483
00:25:25,462 --> 00:25:27,895
I couldn't believe it at first either.

484
00:25:28,394 --> 00:25:31,528
Where is he now?

485
00:25:32,436 --> 00:25:35,469
You just missed him.
He left for Bali this morning.

486
00:25:36,428 --> 00:25:37,428
Bali?

487
00:25:37,454 --> 00:25:40,121
He said he'd take a short break
before starting at the new company.

488
00:25:41,362 --> 00:25:42,395
My goodness...

489
00:25:44,828 --> 00:25:47,295
- Are you okay?
- Thank you.

490
00:25:48,095 --> 00:25:50,095
I just got back from dialysis.

491
00:25:50,928 --> 00:25:51,932
Dialysis?

492
00:25:51,934 --> 00:25:53,934
He said he'd be back on Sunday.

493
00:25:55,228 --> 00:25:57,295
Come in for some tea before you go.

494
00:25:57,828 --> 00:25:58,928
No, thank you.

495
00:26:00,662 --> 00:26:02,328
I'll get going now.

496
00:26:12,628 --> 00:26:14,195
I pretended not to notice your feelings...

497
00:26:15,015 --> 00:26:16,781
because we
hadn't properly established ourselves yet.

498
00:26:17,862 --> 00:26:20,362
I didn't have the time
to think about dating.

499
00:26:21,262 --> 00:26:23,195
But now that we've secured
proper investment,

500
00:26:23,822 --> 00:26:25,455
I'm mustering the courage
to confess my feelings for you.

501
00:26:26,416 --> 00:26:29,816
From now on, I'll handle
all the complicated investment matters.

502
00:26:30,695 --> 00:26:32,728
You just focus on development, Eun Ae.

503
00:26:33,501 --> 00:26:34,501
You trust me, right?

504
00:26:40,795 --> 00:26:41,962
(Lucky Joy Tech Intellectual Property
and Acquisition Agreement)

505
00:26:48,162 --> 00:26:49,195
This can't be.

506
00:26:50,802 --> 00:26:51,935
Then that document was...

507
00:27:07,495 --> 00:27:08,828
(Bali)

508
00:27:25,495 --> 00:27:26,495
What?

509
00:27:27,562 --> 00:27:28,695
How did you find me here?

510
00:27:30,935 --> 00:27:31,935
Darn it!

511
00:27:32,295 --> 00:27:33,295
Hey!

512
00:27:36,228 --> 00:27:37,795
Ji Hun, we need to talk.

513
00:27:38,122 --> 00:27:40,362
- Stop!
- Would you stop if you were me?

514
00:27:41,095 --> 00:27:42,628
If I get caught, I'm dead.

515
00:27:42,828 --> 00:27:43,709
Darn it!

516
00:27:43,711 --> 00:27:45,629
Stop right there!

517
00:27:46,995 --> 00:27:47,995
I said stop, Han Ji Hun!

518
00:27:48,355 --> 00:27:50,022
He's a thief!

519
00:27:50,522 --> 00:27:51,522
Stop right there!

520
00:27:58,095 --> 00:28:00,662
(Our Happy Days)

521
00:28:01,128 --> 00:28:02,928
I saw the article. What happened?

522
00:28:02,928 --> 00:28:03,828
Answer me, now!

523
00:28:03,828 --> 00:28:05,128
Seriously!

524
00:28:05,128 --> 00:28:06,528
What do you think you're doing?

525
00:28:06,528 --> 00:28:07,662
What a crazy guy.

526
00:28:07,662 --> 00:28:09,028
It's my baby...

527
00:28:09,028 --> 00:28:11,362
that I raised
and finally brought into the world.

528
00:28:12,328 --> 00:28:13,895
What are you talking about?

529
00:28:14,062 --> 00:28:15,262
I'm a bit disappointed.

530
00:28:15,262 --> 00:28:17,595
There's a saying,
"You should never take in"...

531
00:28:18,928 --> 00:28:21,262
I never planned to come back,

532
00:28:21,828 --> 00:28:23,095
but here I am again.

533
00:28:23,095 --> 00:28:24,162
I'm not scared.

534
00:28:24,495 --> 00:28:25,495
I'm brave.

535
00:28:26,162 --> 00:28:27,695
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
